  "prompt": "Where can I get a place to stay in goa for a low budget?",
  "response": "Goa offers a variety of budget-friendly accommodation options for travelers. Here are some great places to stay on a low budget:\n\n### 1. **Budget Hostels**\n   - **Goa has many hostels** that are affordable and social. Some popular ones include:\n     - **The Hosteller Goa** (Anjuna, Vagator, and Calangute)\n     - **Goa Backpackers Hostel** (Arambol)\n     - **Zostel Goa** (Calangute and Palolem)\n   - Hostels typically offer dorm beds starting from \u20b9300-800 per night.\n\n### 2. **Guesthouses and Homestays**\n   - **Guesthouses and homestays** are common in Goa and often provide a more local experience. Look for options in areas like:\n     - Arambol\n     - Vagator\n     - Anjuna\n     - Palolem\n   - Prices usually range from \u20b9800-1500 per night.\n\n### 3. **Beach Huts and Shacks**\n   - Many **beach huts** and shacks offer budget accommodation, especially in less crowded areas like:\n     - Arambol\n     - Morjim\n     - Agonda\n   - Beach huts can cost anywhere from \u20b91000-2000 per night.\n\n### 4. **Budget Hotels**\n   - **Budget hotels** are widely available in North and South Goa. Check out areas like:\n     - Calangute\n     - Baga\n     - Candolim\n     - Margao\n   - Rates start from \u20b91000-2000 per night.\n\n### 5. **Campervans and Cottages**\n   - For a unique experience, consider renting a **campervan** or staying in a **cottage**. Check platforms like Airbnb or local rental services for deals.\n\n### 6. **Ashrams and Retreat Centers**\n   - **Ashrams** like the **Brahma Kumaris** or **Art of Living centers** often provide simple, low-cost stays, especially if you\u2019re interested in a spiritual retreat.\n\n### 7. **Off-Season Deals**\n   - Visiting Goa during the **off-season** (May to September) can dramatically reduce costs as many places offer discounts.\n\n### Tips for Finding Budget Stays:\n   - Use platforms like **Booking.com**, **Hostelworld**, **Agoda**, or **Airbnb** to compare prices.\n   - Negotiate rates directly with guesthouses or homestays for better deals.\n   - Look for accommodations slightly **away from tourist hotspots** to save money.\n\nWith a bit of research, you can find comfortable and affordable stays across Goa!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
